				<td colspan="2"><span>If you lack ammo in your ammo slot and CAN use a bow, you get an explicit message telling you that you're out of ammo.  So not having any bard-usable ammo wouldn't keep you from being able to fire a bow - it would just tell you the ammo slot's empty.  I am almost 100% certain that you don't get the out of ammo message if you try to fire a bard equippable bow.  The problem is you have no archery skill, therefore cannnot fire the thing whether you have ammo or not.  And don't ask me to explain the role-play analysis.  It is not logical that ANY class would be unable to fire a bow, even badly.</span></td>
